commit.message: added a wave, attempted to reduce mouse/look sensitivity
refactoring for *days*, cleaned up a lot of duplicate code, move all flags to an enum, fixed mouse clicking/releasing
added melee, moved all flags to an enum
finalized jump and crouch, added fade stub
added regions because turns out that's a thing, changed passing the entire frame to just that hand because that's a little less redundant
added stubs for jump and crouch, cleaned up some duplicate code

even more mouse tweaks, but i'm starting to think this approach is kind of bad, since it still stops in the center while tracking it still awkwardly sort of hits an invisible wall, maybe make it acceleration based or something?
mouse movement tweaks, there's a sort of safe zone in the middle so it's much less jumpy, but the safe zone also gets uh, skipped over, so it's sort of broken
fixed mouse movement listener, it was easier than previously thought, but hasn't been tested ingame yet
